            "id": "4507299",
            "title": "Stock index futures fall as investors assess Tesla results, U.S.-China tariff updates",
            "description": "<html><body><p>Stock index futures inched lower on Thursday, as investors assessed Tesla's (TSLA) earnings and the latest U.S.-China tariff updates, and awaited the September retail inflation numbers slated to come on Friday. </p>\n<p>S&amp;P 500 futures (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/SPX\" title=\"S&amp;P 500 Futures\">SPX</a></span></span></span>) <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">-0.1%</span>, Nasdaq 100 futures (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/US100:IND\" title=\"NASDAQ 100 Futures\">US100:IND</a>) <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">-0.2%</span> and Dow futures (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/INDU\" title=\"Dow Jones Futures\">INDU</a></span></span></span>) <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">-0.2%</span>.</p>\n<p>Wall Street closed lower on Wednesday as investors digested Netflix’s (NFLX) latest earnings results.</p>\n<p>\"Markets struggled for momentum yesterday, with the S&amp;P 500 (-0.53%) falling back after three consecutive gains. The main drivers were fears around the U.S.-China trade situation, weaker earnings announcements, as well as growing concerns about a protracted U.S. government shutdown,\" Deutsche Bank's Henry Allen said. </p>\n<p>Tesla (TSLA) was <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">down 3% </span>in premarket trade after releasing its <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4506957-tesla-warns-on-near-term-uncertainty-ahead-of-acceleration-of-ai-software-and-fleet-based-profits\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Q3 earnings report\">Q3 earnings report</a> as it warned on 'near-term uncertainty.' The firm also missed its profit estimates. </p>\n<p>On the tariffs side, the Trump administration was reportedly <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4507285-trump-admin-mulls-curbs-on-us-software-powered-exports-to-china\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"considering\">considering</a> new restrictions on exports to China involving products made with U.S. software, escalating the ongoing technology and trade standoff between Washington and Beijing.</p>\n<p>The September consumer price index report will be released on Friday, despite the ongoing U.S. government shutdown. The data is expected to show the health of the economy, especially before the Federal Reserve's monetary policy meeting next week.  </p>\n<p>The U.S. government shutdown continued to drag on and became the second-longest in history, as lawmakers remained deadlocked over expiring health-care subsidies.</p>\n<p>\"Indeed, the Polymarket probabilities currently suggest there’s a 75% chance that this will be the longest shutdown in history, so it could be some time before the regular flow of U.S. economic data resumes,\" Allen said. </p>\n<p>Earnings for the day include Intel (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/INTC\" title=\"Intel Corporation\">INTC</a>), Ford Motor Company (NYSE:F), Nokia (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/NOK\" title=\"Nokia Oyj\">NOK</a>),  American Airlines Group (NASDAQ:AAL), Dow Chemical (NYSE:DOW), and Southwest Airlines (NYSE:LUV), among others. </p>\n<h2>Market snapshot as of October 23, 2025 (4:16 am ET)</h2>\n<table data-should-enlarge=\"true\" style=\"width: 611px; height: 272.8px;\">\n<thead><tr style=\"height: 21.2px;\">\n<th style=\"width: 101.35px;\">Category</th>\n<th style=\"width: 208.288px;\">Instrument (Ticker)</th>\n<th style=\"width: 80.0875px;\">Level</th>\n<th style=\"width: 127.625px;\">Change</th>\n<th style=\"width: 78.85px;\">% Change</th>\n</tr></thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 21.2px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 101.35px;\"><strong>Indices</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 208.288px;\">Dow Futures (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/INDU\" title=\"Dow Jones Futures\">INDU</a>)</td>\n<td style=\