            "id": "4507297",
            "title": "European markets mixed as investors brace corporate earnings",
            "description": "<html><body><p><em>Update: The revised post reflects market movements as of 7.30am ET.</em></p> <p>London (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/UKX\" title=\"FTSE 100 Index\">UKX</a>) +0.66% to 9,577. </p> <p>Germany (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/DAX:IND\" title=\"DAX Germany Index\">DAX:IND</a>) -0.08% to 24,130. </p> <p>France (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CAC:IND\" title=\"CAC 40 France Index\">CAC:IND</a>) +0.58% to 8,245. France’s business climate indicator rose to 97 in October 2025 from 96 in September. France’s manufacturing business climate indicator rose to 101 in October 2025 from 97 in September.</p> <p>In other parts of Europe, Norway’s seasonally adjusted unemployment rate edged down to 4.8% in September.</p> <p>Denmark’s consumer confidence index fell to -19.5 in October 2025 from -18.7 in the previous month. </p> <p>The consumer confidence indicator in the Netherlands rose to -27 in October 2025 from -32 in September.</p> <p>The pan-European <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/STOXX\">Stoxx 600</a> (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/STOXX\">STOXX)</a> turned 0.16% higher to 573, as strong corporate earnings lifted investor sentiment.  BP (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/BP\" title=\"BP p.l.c.\">BP</a>) and Shell (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/SHEL\" title=\"Shell plc\">SHEL</a>) were among the best performers amid surging crude prices</p> <p>Gold prices rose to around $4,120 per ounce on Thursday, halting a two-day decline as investors weighed trade developments and geopolitical tensions.</p> <p><strong>In the bond market</strong>, the yield on the US 10-year Treasury was up 4 basis points to 4.00%.</p> <p>Germany's 10-year yield was up 2 basis points to 2.58%.</p> <p>UK's 10-year yield was flat at 4.43%. </p> <p><strong>Currencies:</strong> (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/EUR:USD\" title=\"Euro / US Dollar\">EUR:USD</a>) (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/GBP:USD\" title=\"British Pound / US Dollar\">GBP:USD</a>) (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CHF:USD\" title=\"Swiss Franc / US Dollar\">CHF:USD</a>)</p> <p><strong>ETFs:</strong> (NYSEARCA:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/EWG\">EWG</a>), (NYSE:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/GF\">GF</a>), (NYSEARCA:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/EWI\">EWI</a>), (NYSEARCA:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/EWQ\">EWQ</a>), (NASDAQ:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/FGM\">FGM</a>), (NASDAQ:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/DAX\">DAX</a>), (NYSEARCA:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/FLGR\">FLGR</a>), (NYSEARCA:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/FXB\">FXB</a>), (NYSEARCA:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/EWU\">EWU</a>), (NASDAQ:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/FKU\">FKU</a>), (BATS:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/EWUS\">EWUS</a>), (NYSEARCA:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/FLGB\">FLGB</a>), (NYSEARCA:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/GREK\">GREK</a>)</p> </body></html>",
