            "id": "4507415",
            "title": "Palantir deal with Lumen Technologies worth $200M: report",
            "description": "<html><body><ul>\n<li>Palantir's (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NASDAQ:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/PLTR\" title=\"Palantir Technologies Inc.\">PLTR</a></span>) deal that it signed with Lumen Technologies (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NYSE:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/LUMN\" title=\"Lumen Technologies, Inc.\">LUMN</a></span>) <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4492196-palantir-partners-with-lumen-expands-lear-corp-pact\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"last month\">last month</a> is worth $200M, Bloomberg reported.</li>\n<li>Palantir shares were little changed in premarket trading, while Lumen <span style=\"color: #008000;\">rose 4.7%</span>. </li>\n<li>Terms of the deal will see Lumen spend the $200M with Palantir over a span of several years, the news outlet <a href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-10-23/palantir-inks-more-than-200-million-deal-with-lumen\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"added\">added</a>, citing people familiar with the matter.</li>\n<li>Palantir will provide its Foundry and Artificial Intelligence Platform to Lumen as the latter shifts from a traditional telecom to a next-gen tech infrastructure company.</li>\n</ul>\n</body></html>",
